## Findings

- Nmap efficiently discovers hosts and services.
- Privileges (sudo) are crucial for advanced scans.
- Timing templates and parallelism/rate control adjust speed and stealth.
- Verbosity and debugging provide transparency.
- Saving results in multiple formats supports analysis and automation.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Always run Nmap with proper privileges (sudo) to unlock full scanning capabilities.
- Use moderate timing templates (-T2 or -T3) to balance speed and stealth.
- Limit scans to authorized environments; avoid scanning external networks without permission.
- Save results in multiple formats (-oA) for flexibility in later analysis.
- Start with well-known ports (-p1-1023) before scanning all ports to reduce noise.
- Use verbosity (-v) for learning and debugging, but avoid excessive debugging (-d9) unless necessary.
- Monitor network performance when adjusting parallelism and rate options to prevent packet loss.
- Document findings and validate with additional tools (e.g., Wireshark) for accuracy.

